                    "name": "Caloric Vestibular Stimulation",
                    "description": "Cold water creates a convection current in the semicircular canal of the vestibular apparatus, leading to brief (\\<3 min) and typically well tolerated sense of rotational movement. Similar stimulation is routinely used in standard vestibular diagnostic testing.",
